<h2 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Proportion</h2>
</div>
<strong>Proportion</strong> is a mathematical system of showing how one part is related to another part or to a whole part with respect to the quantity. There are two type of proportion in mathematics;
<br> 
<strong>(i) Direct Proportion </strong> 
<br>
<strong>(ii) Indirect Proportion.</strong>
<br>
In proportion, it is important to use value of one unit to solve the problem (<strong>Unitary Method</strong>).
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Direct Proportion</h3>
</div>
<strong>Direct proportion</strong> refers to when one quantity increases, the other quantity also increases or when one quantity decreases the other quantity also decreases.
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col border-right border-danger">
    <strong>Example 1 </strong>
    <br>
    A worker earns $1200 for working for 16hours. Calculate the payment for (i) 8 hours (ii) 18 hours.
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong> 
    <br>
    Payment for 1 hour = <sup>1200</sup>&frasl;<sub>16</sub> =  <strong>$75</strong>
    <br>
    Working for 8 hours;
    <br>
    8 x $75 = <strong>$600</strong>
    <br>
    Working for 18 hours;
    <br>
    18 x $75 = <strong>$1350</strong>
    <br>
    I.e. it is a <strong>direct proportion</strong>, because the more hours you work, the more money you make.
    </div>
    <div class="col">
    <strong>Example 2</strong>
    <br>
    It cost $ 624 to buy 12 phones, what will it cost to buy 30 of such phones.
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    Cost of one phone = <sup>624</sup>&frasl;<sub>12</sub> = $52
    <br>
    30 caps to will cost = $ 52 x 30 = <strong>$1560</strong>
    <br>
    I.e. it is a <strong>direct proportion</strong>, because the more phones you buy, the more money you pay.
    </div>
