  </div>
  <strong>Inverse proportion</strong> refers to a relationship where one quantity increases as the other quantity decreases vice versa. Inverse proportion is also known as <strong>Indirect Proportion.</strong>
  <br>
  <strong>Example 1</strong>
  <br>
  8 men completed clearing a piece of land in 5days. How long will it take 5 men?
  <br>
  <strong>Solution</strong>
  <br>
  One man will complete the job in 8 x 5 days = <strong>40 days</strong>
  <br>
  5 men will spend = 40 ÷ 5days = <sup>40</sup>&frasl;<sub>5</sub> = <strong>8 days.</strong>
  <br>	
  <strong>Note:</strong> the lesser the number of men, the higher the number of days and the higher the number of men, the lesser the number of days.
  <br>
  <strong>Example 2 </strong>
  <br>
  If it takes 12 planters 8 days to plant 75 mango trees, how long will it take 16 planters to plant the same number of mango tree?
  <br>
  <strong>Solution</strong>
  <br>
  One planter will spend = 12 x 8 = 96 days
  <br>
  16 planters will use = <sup>96</sup>&frasl;<sub>16</sub> = <strong>6 days</strong>
  <br>
  <strong>Example 3</strong>
  <br>
  It can take 20 students 6 days to finish one bag of rice. How many days will it take 15 students to finish one bag?
  <br>
  <strong>Solution</strong>
  <br>
  Days for one student to finish one bag = 20 x 6 = 120 days
  <br>
  15 students will finish it in = <sup>120</sup>&frasl;<sub>15</sub> = <strong>8 days</strong>
