   <br>
   (c) Reciprocal of 0.02 = <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>0.02</sub> = <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> ÷ 0.02 = <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> ÷ <sup>2</sup>&frasl;<sub>100</sub> = <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub>  x <sup>100</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> = <sup>100</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> = 50
   <br>
   (b) Reciprocal of 4<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> = <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub><sup>9</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub></sub> = <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> ÷  <sup>9</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> = <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> x <sup>2</sup>&frasl;<sub>9</sub> = <sup>2</sup>&frasl;<sub>9</sub> = 0.2222
   <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
   <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> Ratio </h3>
   </div>
   <strong>Ratio</strong> is the comparison between quantities of the same kind. Ratio does not have units. The symbol of ratio is <strong>(:).</strong> 
   <strong>Ratio is often use for sharing.</strong>
   <br>
   <div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col border-right border-danger">
    <strong>Example 1</strong>
   <br>
   If Michael has $20 and Paul has $8. What is the ratio of Michael’s money to Paul’s money?
   <br>
   <strong>Solution</strong>
   <br>
   Michael :  Paul
   <br>
   20      :     8
   <br>
   <sup>20</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub>     :    <sup>8</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub>  
   <br>
   Ratio = <b>5</b>       :      <b> 2 </b>
   <br>
  <strong>Example 3</strong>
  <br>
  Three friends A, B, and C want to share $ 180 in the ratio of 5:4:3 respectively. How much does each gets?
  <br>
  <strong>Solution</strong>
  <br>
  Total ratio = 5+4+3 = 12
  <br>
  A = <sup>5</sup>&frasl;<sub>12</sub> x 180 = <sup>900</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> = $75
  <br>
  B = <sup>4</sup>&frasl;<sub>12</sub>  x 180 =  <sup>720</sup>&frasl;<sub>12</sub> = $60
  <br>
  C = 180 – 75 + 60 = 180 – 135 = <strong>$45</strong>
  <br>
  OR
  <br>
  C = <sup>3</sup>&frasl;<sub>12</sub> X 180 = <sup>540</sup>&frasl;<sub>12</sub>  = <strong>$45</strong>
  </div>
    <div class="col">
    <strong>Example 2</strong>
    <br>
    Ronaldo is 12 years old and Messi is 8 years old. They are to share 15 balls in the ratio of their ages. How many balls does one get?
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    <strong>Ronaldo : Messi</strong>
    <br>
    12      :      8
    <br>
    <sup>12</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub>   :      <sup>8</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub>
    <br>
     Ratio = <strong>3       :     2</strong>
    <br>
    <strong>Total ratio</strong> = 3 + 2 = 5
    <br>
    Ronaldo’s share = <sup>3</sup>&frasl;<sub>5</sub> x 15 = <sup>3</sup>&frasl;<sub>1</sub> x 3 = <strong>9 balls.</strong>
    <br>
    Messi’s share = 15 – 9 = <strong>6 balls</strong>
    </div>
